    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "There was an associated change\r\n\r\n\"Verify `repeat_hash(block.randao_reveal, proposer.randao_layers) == proposer.randao_commitment`\" used to read \"Verify `repeat_hash(block.randao_reveal, proposer.randao_layers + 1) == proposer.randao_commitment`\"\r\n\r\nNotice the `+1` was removed. In the case where the proposer does indeed propose a block at the slot they were designated and they had no previous skips, their `randao_layers` will be 1 and thus just one layer of the hash onion will need to be provided.\r\n\r\nThis is nice because it cleanly separated the per-slot operations and per-block operations.",
